+++ b/docs/expose-upload.md
@@ -0,0 +1,82 @@
+# Exposé Upload
+
+Estate Scout42 supports creating rental-property listings directly in the
+browser. The feature is intended for the demo application and does not require
+an account or backend service.
+
+![Image upload step in the property listing form](assets/expose-upload-lifecycle.png)
+
+## Related standard
+
+The current image representation follows the `data:` URL structure defined by
+[RFC 2397](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc2397).
+
+![Condensed RFC 2397 reference with syntax and examples](assets/rfc-2397-reference.png)
+
+## Opening the upload flow
+
+Use **List property** in the navigation or open `/exposes/new`. The form is
+split into four steps so validation feedback stays close to the relevant
+fields:
+
+1. **Basics** collects the title, property type, complete address, and
+   description.
+2. **Details** collects rent, area, rooms, floor, availability, pet policy, and
+   internet speed.
+3. **Images** accepts and arranges the property photos.
+4. **Preview** presents the resulting listing before publication.
+
+The Back button preserves all entered values. Cancel returns to the property
+results without storing a listing. Publication only happens from the final
+preview step.
+
+## Field validation
+
+All fields from the shared `Property` interface are required. The form applies
+the following rules:
+
+- Titles require at least 8 characters and allow up to 100.
+- Addresses require a street section and a comma-separated city section.
+- Descriptions require at least 40 characters and allow up to 1,500.
+- Warm rent, living space, rooms, floor, and internet speed must be positive
+  numbers within the ranges shown by validation errors. Ground floor uses `0`.
+- The availability date must be today or later.
+- Pet permission is represented by a checkbox.
+
+Validation runs before moving to the next step. Invalid fields remain on the
+current step and show an English error message.
+
+## Image handling
+
+Each listing requires between 1 and 8 images. Supported formats are JPEG, PNG,
+and WebP, with a maximum size of 5 MB per image.
+
+Images can be selected through the file picker or dropped on the upload area.
+Every accepted image receives a preview and controls to:
+
+- move it left or right in the gallery;
+- set it as the cover image;
+- remove it before publication.
+
+The first image is always the cover image used in search results. The remaining
+order is preserved in the detail-page gallery. Unsupported, oversized, and
+excess files are rejected with an accessible error message.
+
+## After publication
+
+A successful publication redirects to the new detail page. The listing also
+appears immediately:
+
+- in the main property results;
+- in city filtering when its city is selected;
+- under `/my-exposes`.
+
+Use **My listings** to see entries created in the current browser and delete an
+entry. Deletion requires confirmation and does not affect the static records in
+`app/data/exposes.json`.
+
+## Browser-local limitation
+
+Uploaded listings are available only in the browser profile that created them.
+They are not synchronized to another browser, device, private browsing session,
+or user account. Clearing site data removes local listings and their images.
diff --git a/docs/local-property-storage.md b/docs/local-property-storage.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0b2be54
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/local-property-storage.md
@@ -0,0 +1,91 @@
+# Local Property Storage
+
+## Architecture
+
+The upload feature uses the browser's IndexedDB API. This keeps the React demo
+self-contained while allowing listings and images to survive page reloads and
+browser restarts.
+
+![Exposé upload architecture and data flow](assets/expose-upload-architecture.png)
+
+`app/data/property-store.ts` owns persistence and exposes:
+
+- `usePropertyStore()` for reactive property, loading, and error state;
+- `createLocalProperty()` for publication;
+- `deleteLocalProperty()` for removal;
+- `refreshProperties()` for re-reading browser data.
+
+No additional npm package is required.
+
+## Database layout
+
+The database is named `estate-scout42`, currently at version `1`. It contains a
+single object store named `properties` with `id` as its key path.
+
+Local records use the shared `Property` shape plus metadata:
+
+| Field | Purpose |
+| --- | --- |
+| `id` | UUID generated at publication time |
+| `images` | Ordered image Data URLs; the first value is the cover |
+| `created_at` | ISO timestamp used to sort newest listings first |
+| `source` | Set to `local` for browser-created entries |
+
+Static JSON entries are normalized in memory with `source: "static"` and an
+`images` array containing their existing `main_image`. Static records are never
+written to IndexedDB.
+
+## Combined read model
+
+The store initially exposes static properties so the application remains
+useful while IndexedDB opens. It then loads local records, sorts them by
+creation time, and publishes a combined list:
+
+```text
+local properties, newest first
+static JSON properties, existing order
+```
+
+Search results, city options, and detail lookup consume this combined list.
+`My listings` consumes only `localProperties`.
+
+Subscribers are notified through `useSyncExternalStore`. Creating, deleting,
+or manually refreshing a record updates every mounted consumer without a page
+reload.
+
+## Slugs and identity
+
+Existing static properties keep their title-derived URL slug. Local properties
+append the first eight characters of their UUID:
+
+```text
+/exposes/bright-apartment-with-city-views-a1b2c3d4
+```
+
+This prevents two browser-created properties with identical titles from
+colliding while preserving old static URLs.
+
+## Image persistence
+
+The upload component reads accepted image files as Data URLs before
+publication. IndexedDB stores those strings inside the property record. This is
+simple and portable for a demo, but less space-efficient than binary Blob
+storage or an object-storage service.
+
+The UI limits uploads to 8 images and 5 MB per original file to reduce browser
+storage pressure. Actual quotas vary by browser, available disk space, and
+privacy mode.
+
+## Failures and recovery
+
+The store reports a readable error when IndexedDB is unavailable, blocked, or
+full. Quota errors recommend deleting a local listing or selecting smaller
+images.
+
+When loading local data fails, static properties remain visible. Failed writes
+do not redirect and leave the completed form available for correction or retry.
+Failed deletion leaves the listing visible and shows an error on `My listings`.
+
+Clearing site data is destructive and cannot be recovered because there is no
+server copy. A production implementation should replace this store with an
+authenticated API and external image storage.
